81
00:05:08,750 --> 00:05:10,000
two are Jordan blocks--

82
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:12,580

83
00:05:12,580 --> 00:05:15,600
they're not Jordan blocks,
they're matrices in Jordan

84
00:05:15,600 --> 00:05:17,840
normal form.

85
00:05:17,840 --> 00:05:20,530
They're different matrices in
Jordan normal form, so they

86
00:05:20,530 --> 00:05:23,350
will not be similar.

87
00:05:23,350 --> 00:05:27,060
But let's actually see why.

88
00:05:27,060 --> 00:05:29,400
Let's look at--

89
00:05:29,400 --> 00:05:32,770
remember one of the things that
similarity preserves are

90
00:05:32,770 --> 00:05:34,790
eigenvectors and eigenvalues.

91
00:05:34,790 --> 00:05:38,810
So let's look at the eigenspace
with eigenvalue

92
00:05:38,810 --> 00:05:41,710
minus one with these
two matrices.

93
00:05:41,710 --> 00:05:48,010
So J1 plus the identity--

94
00:05:48,010 --> 00:05:50,720
let's look at the nullspace
of this matrix.

95
00:05:50,720 --> 00:05:59,730
So this is just 0's on the
diagonal and 1's right above

96
00:05:59,730 --> 00:06:05,530
the diagonal, and J2
plus the identity.

97
00:06:05,530 --> 00:06:09,790
This is just 0, 1, 0, 0.

98
00:06:09,790 --> 00:06:12,350

99
00:06:12,350 --> 00:06:20,550
So the point is that the
nullspace of this matrix is

100
00:06:20,550 --> 00:06:22,050
just one dimensional.

101
00:06:22,050 --> 00:06:25,570
So there's only one independent
eigenvector of J1

102
00:06:25,570 --> 00:06:29,880
with eigenvalue minus 1 whereas
the nullspace of this

103
00:06:29,880 --> 00:06:31,900
matrix is two dimensional.

104
00:06:31,900 --> 00:06:36,550

105
00:06:36,550 --> 00:06:39,230
There are two independent
eigenvectors with

106
00:06:39,230 --> 00:06:41,130
eigenvalue minus 1.

107
00:06:41,130 --> 00:06:44,520
So the dimension--

108
00:06:44,520 --> 00:06:46,170
the nullspace--

109
00:06:46,170 --> 00:06:54,650
of J1 plus the identity, this
is 1, and this is 2.

110
00:06:54,650 --> 00:06:58,880
So they cannot possibly
be similar.

111
00:06:58,880 --> 00:07:02,890

112
00:07:02,890 --> 00:07:03,200
Good.

113
00:07:03,200 --> 00:07:04,820
So that completes the problem.

114
00:07:04,820 --> 00:07:08,030
It's a nice exercise to do
