115
00:07:08,030 --> 00:07:11,910
And you can use these techniques
not just looking at

116
00:07:11,910 --> 00:07:17,020
the number of independent
eigenvectors and the nullspace

117
00:07:17,020 --> 00:07:22,410
of your J minus lambda I matrix,
but also powers of J

118
00:07:22,410 --> 00:07:24,710
minus lambda I and
their nullspaces.

119
00:07:24,710 --> 00:07:29,660
You can use this to show that
any two matrices in Jordan

120
00:07:29,660 --> 00:07:33,500
normal form that are different
